Mr. DAVIN. I would have moved that these amendments be not agreed to, but I had a conver— sation with the Hon. Mr. Dewdney, who tells me that certain changes will be made which will, I think, be quite satisfactory to the North-\Vest.-

Mr. LAURIER.
